From b0ee565b4654f384f06f87ff1af08e511627a283 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Micheal Waltz <micheal@ecliptik.com>
Date: Sun, 26 Apr 2026 17:11:56 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] [DOSKUTSU] dos: comprehensive mode-set lifecycle trace + log
 writer coordination (lever 1 diag)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Phase 9 lever 1 wave 2 diagnostic. Wave 1 capture (gateway4, real Mach64
HW, 2026-04-26) revealed two issues with the patch 0008 lifecycle trace:

1. Patch 0008 only caught the FINAL CreateWindowFramebuffer invocation —
   earlier mode-sets did not visibly trigger the [lifecycle] handlers, so
   we couldn't tell whether the SDL3 surface-recreation lifecycle ran for
   the splash-screen mode-set, NXEngine's window-create mode-set, etc.

2. Two log writers raced and produced a truncated/interleaved log line:
     "DOSVESA-MODESET: ... lfb_[lifecycle] CreateWindowFramebuffer:"
   fsync-per-write doesn't help: each FILE* (one in SDL_dosmodes.c, one
   in SDL_dosframebuffer.c, one in SDL_video.c, one for the older
   DOSVESA-FB-* trace) had its own libc buffer, so lines from one writer
   could land mid-line of another.

Patch 0009 fixes both.

Log writer coordination
-----------------------

New shared writer in src/video/dos/SDL_dosdbg.{c,h} exposes a single
funnel function `doskutsu_dbg_log(fmt, ...)` that holds ONE FILE* on
/sdldbg.log and emits one fprintf+fflush+fsync per call. All four
existing writers in the DOS backend + SDL_video.c are migrated to it:

  - DOSVESA-MODESET / DOSVESA-MODELIST / DOSVESA-CTRL (SDL_dosmodes.c)
  - [lifecycle] (SDL_dosframebuffer.c CreateWindow/Invalidate/Update +
    SDL_video.c GetWindowSurface/OnWindowResized/CheckPixelSizeChanged/
    OnWindowPixelSizeChanged)
  - DOSVESA-FB-INIT/CALL/VRAM/NORMAL (SDL_dosframebuffer.c)

Per-line prefix tags are kept verbatim so existing greps still work.

Comprehensive mode-set lifecycle trace
--------------------------------------

Three new traces added to SDL_dosmodes.c DOSVESA_SetDisplayMode:

  - "mode-set #N (entry): requested id=0xNNNN WxH bpp= ... (prev id=0xX)"
    fires at the very top of every SetDisplayMode call, before the
    no-op-when-mode-id-matches early return. Sequence counter so we can
    correlate with downstream CreateWindowFramebuffer #N traces.

  - "mode-set #N (no-op): mode_id matches current ..." when the early
    return fires (so a mode-set that DIDN'T trigger CreateWindowFramebuffer
    is visibly attributable).

  - "LFB-decision #N: hint_allow_direct=X lfb_available=X
     is_banked_usable=X -> use_lfb=X" fires immediately before the VBE
    INT 10h SetMode call. Makes the policy decision (LFB vs banked)
    explicit and per-call, rather than implicit in the
    DOSVESA-MODESET trailer. Sets up the diagnostic for patch 0010,
    which adds SDL_HINT_DOS_PREFER_LFB to flip the decision the other
    way.

  - "mode-set #N (exit ok): banked_mode=X mapping.size=X page_flip=X"
    at the end of SetDisplayMode so the trace reads cleanly entry → exit.

CreateWindowFramebuffer is also now sequence-counted with entry + exit
log lines (replacing patch 0008's single-line trace), so we see EVERY
invocation regardless of how the surface lifecycle chains downstream.

Why DOS needs this
------------------

DOS-only diagnostics for tracing the SDL3-DOS framebuffer + mode-set
lifecycle path. Required to pick between the lever-1 implementation
paths (A: backend manual lifecycle, B: lazy re-init in
UpdateWindowFramebuffer, C: idempotent CreateWindowFramebuffer, D:
NXEngine-side renderer recreation) — see docs/PHASE9-15FPS-PLAN.md
§3 Lever 1.4. SDL_video.c additions are guarded by
SDL_VIDEO_DRIVER_DOSVESA so non-DOS builds aren't perturbed.

Local-only patch per workspace policy (memory note "SDL upstream —
local patches only"): never PR'd upstream, sidestepping
vendor/SDL/CLAUDE.md's no-AI-PRs restriction.

